subject: [] Any
note:
Property type = actant1, property value/target = actant2. Some attributes can have time, e.g. someone can be a resident of Milan (or be unmarried and then married) at some time. Also location is allowed, e.g. one can have the office of "inquisitor heretice pravitatis" in Lombardy and March of Genoa. Technically, these are A/R properties (A/R modifiers): they do not pertain to the inquisitor but to the "has" predicate.
The label of A0093 was "has attribute", then "has property", then "has only" (see https://docs.google.com/document/d/1GMAsDJJIa4YuOKwiDLQKt6pSPud71lhUNf3sb6XkGyU/edit# for the history of and reasons for changes).
